Auth route 
    GET-  is used for authenticating a token that the client has(through registration or login) and returns user details
    POST- used for logging in and provides a token as result, to authenticate in auth
User is used for regestering a user and receiving a token as result, to authenticate in auth

POST /api/users = register a user => token
POST /api/auth = login a user => token

GET /api/auth(token) = validate token => logged in user details

Add auth middleware to enable token expecting system that returns details